                            <comment id="476889" author="JIRAUSER19288" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2025 15:50:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As Jian mentioned, this issue stopped occurring about a month ago.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nevertheless, I&apos;ve looked into the (now known duplicate &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19366&quot; title=&quot;sanity-sec test_73: name  in CREAT is not short=a&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19366&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-19366&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) where it seems that both tests (35 and 73) failed due to the same issue. Both tests register changelog users, which at first appear to succeed. However, when the changelog is cleared or, in the case of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19366&quot; title=&quot;sanity-sec test_73: name  in CREAT is not short=a&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19366&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-19366&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, no activity from the user is logged for FS operations, the tests failed. In both cases, this happened on MDT0000 where the changelog user was not being created. Please refer to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19366?focusedId=476865&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-476865&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;my comment in LU-19366&lt;/a&gt; for further details on this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="474487" author="yujian" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2025 20:41:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The subtests have passed consistently on master branch since 2025-10-02.&lt;br/&gt;
Let me remove this ticket from the tstu list. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
